itemDescription: British air racer in the 1930s and a test pilot for Vickers Armstrong in the Second World War. Aviator, Author, and Businessman.

wikipedia_page.main: Alexander Adolphus Dumphries Henshaw,  (7 November 1912 – 24 February 2007) was a British air racer in the 1930s and a test pilot for Vickers Armstrong during the Second World War.
